results.title: The Enemy Within
results.description: Mystique impersonates a senator's wife for her own sinister purposes.

results.title: The Mutant Program!
results.description: Master Mold comes after Cyclops; Angel's wings are amputated.

results.title: Going Home
results.description: Shard hops through her future and joins Xavier's Underground Enforcers.

results.title: Horrors From the Future in Today's World
Dreams of Tomorrow
results.description: Archer, Greystone and Fixx travel to the present; Shard leaves X-Factor to go after them.

results.title: Give Me Shelter
results.description: Full origin of Wildchild and his relationship with Val.

results.title: The Fall of the Brotherhood Part 1
results.description: The rogue X.S.E. agents from the future inhabit bodies in the present day and track down Mystique; Havok forcefully begins his bid to disband the Brotherhood, but has to face Mystique and the future mutants to do so.

results.title: Points of View
results.description: The Brotherhood is disbanded and Havok forms a new X-Factor.

results.title: Phantoms
results.description: Havok tries to pull his new team together, but the future mutants are off to kill a kidnapped boy who will grow up to be a tyrant.

results.title: Fairie Light
results.description: The X-Factor members try to get their lives together and end up trying to save the family of the man whose body Archer inhabits from Madripoor agents sent to kill him.

results.title: Bashed!
results.description: Shard tries to help a young boy suspected of being a mutant from being bullied by his peers.

results.title: Sorry Is The Hardest Word!
results.description: Gyrich tries to arrest Havok for crimes against the government using Mandroids as backup; Polaris helps keep this from happening.

results.title: Times Change
results.description: In trying to return to his own timeline, Greystone goes crazy and causes an accident that will dismantle X-Factor forever.

results.title: Whose Death Is It, Anyway?
results.description: The Morlocks return to the tunnels; Scott is shown Maddie's corpse in Alaska and returns home to try and help Angel; Apocalypse continues to gather his Horsemen; A forlorn (and wingless) Angel leaves the hospital and takes off in a plane that explodes over the ocean.

results.title: Playing With Fire!
results.description: Rusty tries to work out a deal with Masque to heal the woman he burned in issue #1.

results.title: Die, Mutants, Die!
results.description: X-Factor tries to save San Francisco from being shaken apart by Rictor; Hodge is revealed as a traitor.

results.title: The Enemy Within
results.description: Hodge tries to drive Cyclops crazy by making him believe that Jean is Phoenix; Apocalypse begins Angel's transformation.

results.title: All Together Now!
results.description: Apocalypse tries to teach his Horsemen teamwork by turning them loose on X-Factor; Pestilence touches Beast making him deathly ill; During the battle, Iceman freezes a good portion of Central Park.

results.title: Bless the Beasts and Children
results.description: Tower kidnaps Beast for Dr. Carl Maddicks who begins experiments on him; X-Factor searches for their friend.

results.title: Children's Crusade
results.description: The X-Factor kids clean up Iceman's mess in Central Park

results.title: For Every Action...
results.description: X-Factor fires Hodge; Warren's will is read and all of his money is left to X-Factor through Hodge; The Right attacks.

results.title: If I Should Die...
results.description: The Right captures Rictor again and tries to use his powers for destruction; Cameron Hodge reveals himself as The Commander of the Right.

results.title: You Say You Want Some Evolution?
results.description: X-Factor goes up against Hodge and The Right to try to rescue their young charges who have been kidnapped.

results.title: Masks
results.description: X-Factor confronts Apocalypse on his Ship and learn that Warren has become the Archangel of Death; X-Factor is captured; The Horsemen take off to wreak havoc on New York; Caliban, lured by the promise of real power, joins Apocalypse.

results.title: Judgement Day!
results.description: Archangel breaks his programming and rejoins X-Factor; X-Factor defeats Apocalypse and causes his ship to crash land in New York.

results.title: Casualties
results.description: X-Factor helps New York recover from the Horsemen's attack; The team moves into Apocalypse's ship and gets new costumes.

results.title: Gifts!
results.description: X-Factor distributes gifts on Christmas.

results.title: Countdown!
results.description: X-Factor fights and frees Apocalypse's sentient ship from its former master's control.

results.title: Regression Obsession
results.description: X-Factor catches up to the captured Beast to find that Maddicks' experiments have caused him to lose his fur; Angel changes to a brown and white costume.

results.title: The Carbon Copy Avengers
results.description: X-Factor battles aliens disguised as Avengers.

results.title: For All The World To See
results.description: The junior members of X-Factor prepare to head off to school; The Alliance protests the Mutant Registration Act by wanton destruction and runs up against X-Factor; Beast returns to his blue and furry form and regains the use of his mind; Freedom Force takes the Alliance into custody and makes X-Factor sign the Registration Act; Rusty agrees to turn himself in.

results.title: Death!
results.description: Archangel tries to save Candy from Hodge and his demon allies.

results.title: Go To The Orphan Maker!
results.description: Jean and Scott rescue Nathan Christopher from Nanny.

results.title: Duet!
results.description: Jean fights Maddie to the death and learns that she was a clone of herself created by Mr. Sinister.

results.title: Ashes to Ashes
results.description: The X-Men and X-Factor tackle Sinister and find out that he raised and conditioned Cyclops as a boy.

results.title: Golden Boy!
results.description: X-Factor tries to rescue Alchemy who has been kidnapped by trolls

results.title: All That Glitters...
results.description: X-Factor has been captured by the trolls, but they manage to free themselves. Alchemy stops the menace of the trolls.

results.title: Kidnaped! (Judgement War Part One)
results.description: X-Factor's ship is transported to another planet, where they're caught in the middle of a battle, and they end up divided.

results.title: Another World! (Judgement War Part Two)
results.description: The members of X-Factor, still divided, try to understand more about the planet and the raging war

results.title: Arena! (Judgement War Part Three)
results.description: Archangel is forced to fight in the arena, while Iceman defeats Lord Rask

results.title: From The Depths of Memory... Come The Depths Of Pain!
Exchange (Judgement War Part Four)
results.description: The Beast find Marvel Girl, while Scott's son Christopher is taken by Lord Rand

results.title: Guardian
results.description: While he's imprisoned by the Chosen, Archangel remembers an old adventure.

results.title: Power Struggle (Judgement War Part Six)
results.description: Iceman and Archangel are forced to fight each other in the Arena, but in the end they manage to turn against Lord Rask.

results.title: X-Factor vs. the Alliance of Evil
